extendedDecimalScope1And2And3GhgEmission.prompt:
Extract the total Scope 1, Scope 2, and Scope 3 greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions in tonnes from the following text. Scope 1 emissions are direct GHG emissions from sources owned or controlled by the company. Scope 2 emissions are indirect energy-related GHG emissions from purchased electricity, steam, heating, cooling, or other externally generated energy sources, preferably calculated using the location-based method and the equity share approach. Scope 3 emissions include all other indirect upstream and downstream GHG emissions across the company’s value chain, as defined by the GHG Protocol. Instructions: 1. If the text provides explicit numeric values for Scope 1, Scope 2 (location-based), and Scope 3, first remove any commas or other formatting from the numbers, then sum them and return the total. 2. If any individual value is missing, check if a combined Scope 1–3 total is explicitly stated and return that. 3. Always select the most recent year if multiple annual values are reported. 4. Only extract absolute emissions in tonnes (t or tCO2e); ignore intensity metrics, ratios, or partial totals. 5. Exclude any partial totals unless a distinct Scope 1–2–3 total is provided as a fallback. Return rules: - Return only the numeric value, without units, symbols, or descriptive text. - Use a dot as the decimal separator and do not use thousand separators. - If multiple totals are present, return the most explicit or most recent value. - If neither the sum nor a combined total can be determined, return null.

